    // `a_0, ..., a_k` can be made `0, 1, ..., k`. (Requires `a_i >= i` for `0 <= i <= k`)
    // `a_k, ..., a_{n-1}` can be made `k, k-1, ..., 0`. (Requires `a_i >= k - (i-k)` for `k <= i < n`, and `k-(i-k) >= 0`)
